##Stay in the empty theater, I still wait for the arrival of the Lion King

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

Huazhong University of Science and Technology School of Journalism and communication

Wen Zi (not her real name) , the manager of a children's eye clinic, remembers listening to a concert by Li Yundi at Qintai Theater in Wuhan in October 2019. She missed those moments (previously reported) . Today, the theater, along with the rest of Wuhan, is silent.

"If it hadn't been for this outbreak, we would have had a crazy day, " said Zhou Dengtao, the theater's security manager, as he and his colleagues huddled in the theater's Office for a chat. It was a special day, a 32-day stay at the theatre, and no matter how monotonous the time was, they were still filled with emotions about February 19th.

The original Broadway musical "the Lion King" was originally scheduled to premiere on February 19 at the Wuhan International Tour Station. Due to the new pneumonia outbreak, it was announced that it had been cancelled and the ticket refund channel was opened recently. The re-run time is unknown.

Seven security guards, including Zhou Dengtao, did not return home after the early holiday on Jan. 18 at the Qintai Grand Theater in Wuhan, where they stayed. They are Wuhan or Wuhan surrounding people, most of the 90, the youngest 22-year-old, are healthy, strong immune young men.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
From last year, "look at the Cherry Blossom, see the Lion King, " "Tour Wuhan, see the Lion King, " these slogans let Zhou Dengtao feel excited. All images in this article are provided for the interviewees

Seven men, three shifts a day for 32 days, now guard and will continue to guard the once glittering, bustling theater lobby. Until the epidemic is over, the theater will be their home.

Zhou Dengtao was born in 1983, Hubei Xiaogan Zougang town United Village, his eyes of the Grand Theater is an elegant beautiful temple, is his deep love of the place.

"It's sacred to work in a theater, " said Zhou, who has always been uncommunicative and plain-spoken. As if they were behind the scenes and had nothing to do with the drama on stage, they were already closely connected to the theatre and the arts, and their emotions took root here, even though the tragedy was merciless and the theatre was silent, it's still a profession they enjoy and take pride in.

To "the Lion King. "

Without the disaster, the focus of Wuhan will be on the Qintai Grand Theatre on February 19, the first mainland premiere of "the Lion King" , which will be staged more than 70 times over the next few months. Wuhan in spring will belong to "the Little Lion. ".

It's not an exaggeration. After touring many countries and breaking box office records, "the Lion King" finally arrived in mainland China. On the first day of ticket sales at the Wuhan Station, nearly 10,000 tickets were sold, and nearly 40 percent of the audience wanted to see the play from other cities in Wuhan, staff at the Qintai theatre said it was "an unprecedented miracle" .

For Zhou, the Lion King is one of the most exciting and anticipated projects of his nearly six-year career, and his security department has been preparing and rehearsing for the lion king's security work since last year.

"Are all the posts in place? Is the inspection complete? " In Zhou's imagination, originally tonight at 6:30 pm on February 19th at 6:30 pm, his uniform was stiff and his shoes were shiny. He should have been using his walkie-talkie to connect with his posts. The doors of the hall will open, and audiences from all over the country will be greeted by their orderly entry, and the audience will be attracted by the variety of Lion King promotional materials that will fill the hall. This will be the moment everyone has been waiting for, it will also be a great honour for Zhou Dengtao in his career.

Since last year, Zhou Dengtao has been excited by such slogans as "see the cherry blossoms, see the Lion King" and "go to Wuhan, see the Lion King" . This is a project supported by the Wuhan Municipal Government, the municipal administration of Culture and tourism, and it is the city's calling card to be built in Wuhan, and he'll be there to greet the cast and crew from afar. "It makes so much sense! " He said.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
For Zhou, who has been in the business for nearly six years, the lion king is one of his most exciting and anticipated projects

Like all Qintai workers, Zhou Dengtao was sorry, but he was saddened to think that many families in Wuhan had been broken up in the disaster, he understood that the common struggle against the epidemic was the most important thing at this time.

As a veteran of the war, Zhou sometimes wondered if the virus was an enemy and he would fight it in the field with a gun.

We're not sitting on an island

Responding to the company's call to stay in the theater, Zhou Dengtao never hesitated. After graduating from high school and enlisting in the army, he left after 12 years in the army, and on Youth Day he took a job at the Poly Group, where the Qintai Opera House is located.

Veteran more, good atmosphere, military management, here to make Zhou Dengtao feel solid and substantial. "I am the head of the security department. I should come to the theatre at this time. This is the place I should guard. " He thought that was enough.

February 19 is no different than the previous 32 days. At 9:00 in the morning, he arrived at his post on time, went to the kitchen to help with the work, cut the vegetables, carry the dishes, take out the sterilized bowls and chopsticks, and then began to go to each post inspection, engineering room, stage equipment to check, the monitoring room and the high-voltage distribution room should ensure that someone on duty.

About 11 am, they prepared to eat, and the Music Hall Next Door Qintai staff with the stay. Theatre canteens are outsourced to catering companies and have their own vegetable bases where they can eat fresh fruit and vegetables every day. The Poly Group had brought in supplies from around the country and overseas, as well as supplies of face masks, hand sanitizer, hand sanitizer and gloves.

After lunch should be cleaned and disinfected, office, Control Room, kitchen, bathroom... during the epidemic, living areas and work areas to ensure daily disinfection. After dinner, they need to collect all the garbage and send it to the outdoor collection point. At 8 p.m. , the night shift arrives for another 12 hour shift.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Ensure daily disinfection of living and working areas

Wuhan epidemic was very optimistic, but adequate supplies are the source of Zhou Dengtao's sense of security, the theater of the world at least let them live worry-free. Zhou receives almost daily phone calls from the group's leaders, asking about health and supplies. He can feel that they are cared for, not guarding an isolated island here, that reassured him: "You can do your job better with no worries. "

The auditorium is large, more than 1,400 square meters, three floors and 1,802 seats. Zhou Dengtao often looks at the empty theater and thinks of the noisy pictures of singing and dancing in the past. He said to himself: "when the epidemic is over, you can happily come to the theater, perform, see the play, meet the audience! "

I love the theater and I love Wuhan

Stay in the period of the density of work is not high, most of the time still need to spend in life trivial. Zhou has plenty of time at his disposal, apart from keeping the theater safe and ensuring the health of the staff.

Colleagues often relax, chat and play games in the office. Besides helping out in the kitchen, Zhou also watches movies and TV shows. He has watched all 64 episodes of "the Great Ming Dynasty. " Stephen Chow and Andy Lau also saw a lot of early films. He also loved to read books, the characters of a dream of Red Mansions that had fascinated him, and Deng Xiaoping's daughter's my father, Deng Xiaoping, and Ji Xianlin's diary of a cowshed, which he read over and over, history books always appealed to him.

Before he goes to bed in recent days, he listens to books on an APP, pays $365 for a full year subscription, and listens to 50 minutes or so of audio, condensed from various classics, about motivation, growth, business management, sales and marketing, when his eyes are tired, he feels comfortable listening to books. "Now we have less and less time to read, and it's all fragmented time, so listening to a book makes it easier to get into it, " he said. He was eager to recommend this interesting thing to those around him.

Zhou Dengtao has feelings for the theatre. As a child, he could only see symphonic concerts and plays on television. Before coming to work here, he always felt like an outsider and out of place in the theater. But over the past five or six years, he found that whether it is drama, musical or symphony, are in the soil of life bloom, he can always see the shadow of life. On duty, he and his colleagues often take turns working on the floor, where he watches each scene from beginning to end and is touched by it. In his opinion, Notre Dame and Aida are stunning works, a Tale of love and hate.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In Zhou Dengtao's eyes, the Grand Theater is an elegant and beautiful temple, a place he deeply loves.

For Zhou Dengtao, the spiritual life is more important than the material life, he felt that only the spiritual enrichment, spiritual satisfaction can let a person full of sunshine and happiness. He remembers an old woman who came to the show with her grandson every day last summer. She bought only one ticket and asked the theater staff to bring her grandson in. She sat outside and waited. She said she was a neighbor, and the grandson was learning the piano, she was also a fan of children's plays, and she believed in the theater, letting son's son; Grandson Watch as many shows as she could. Zhou Dengtao more feel that Wuhan is actually a very good cultural atmosphere of the city, everyone on the art and cultural demand is high, is these special audience let him more and more know the city.

In a disaster in which most people in Wuhan Struggle Daily for Food, stock and supplies, the theater seems to represent only the ivory tower of the spiritual world and cultural life, and the Grand Theater is doomed to be temporarily silent because of the epidemic, duration unknown. But the reality is surprising. "spring flowers bloom, the theater meets" seems to have become the secret word between Qintai and Wuhan audiences. This sentence can be found everywhere in the message area of all platforms of Qintai Grand Theater. Everyone is doubly confident because of this romantic agreement, including Zhou:

"The theatre is a very important part of the city, and while the epidemic is serious, I believe there are some things that will not be forgotten. "

Many people who have bought the Lion King do not want to refund their tickets. They are waiting for the return of the Lion King. So is Zhou Dengtao. He is sure that it will be staged. He is waiting for that day in the theater.
